      <para id="id15069544">8. Impenetrable rock</para>
      <para id="id29365436">Sedimentary rock formations:</para>
      <para id="id30084119"><emphasis effect="underline">Layers</emphasis> of rock on the <emphasis effect="underline">earth's surface</emphasis> and <emphasis effect="underline">under water</emphasis>. <emphasis effect="underline">Formed by debris </emphasis>or <emphasis effect="underline">earlier life</emphasis>. Debris type forms through the <emphasis effect="underline">breaking up of rocks</emphasis> and the scattering of the <emphasis effect="underline">pieces</emphasis> by <emphasis effect="underline">wind and water</emphasis> to lower levels where they form <emphasis effect="underline">sand and mud</emphasis>. The ones formed by earlier life are created by the <emphasis effect="underline">compression of skeletons</emphasis> to form <emphasis effect="underline">limestone</emphasis>.</para>
    </section>
